    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-07T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-07T20:00:00-05:00" n="109"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/721: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sparks</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-07T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 7, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:56 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>238. During my call on the President this evening he gave categorical
                    instructions to the Chief of Police to take immediately additional steps to
                    guard against possible attempts at sabotage and to apprehend any person showing
                    any suspicious movement. While there are no Japanese in this country he gave
                    these orders in recognition of the collaboration of Japan and Germany as Axis
                    partners and the possibility of attempt at sabotage by Germans.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sparks</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
